Definition: a witness whose relationship to the opposing party is such that his or her testimony may be prejudiced against the opposing party
Example: a hostile witness can be asked leading questions and cross-examined
Synonyms: hostile_witness, witness, a, whose, relationship, to, the, opposing, party, is, such, that, his, or, her, testimony, may, be, prejudiced, against, hostile, can, asked, leading, questions, and, cross-examined
Category: noun.person
